      "seed": 564688749,
      "version": 136,
      "versionNonce": 158403036,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "High level design goal is to create a simple design that satisfies our above 3 functional\nrequirements.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "High level design goal is to create a simple design that satisfies our above 3 functional\nrequirements.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BzUMl_55fcZlTrh7PUVHE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1819.287774845846,
      "y": 6080.549198136332,
      "width": 2474.998291015625,
      "height": 900,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bDQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1296514787,
      "version": 2017,
      "versionNonce": 1231163876,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "First thing in our design is going to have a client. Its going to be a User thats interfacing with our service. and then we\nare going to opt for a microservices architecture this is by default is most common setup in these types of interviews. If \nwe are not sure which architecture we go with Microservice is probably the right choice.\n\nApI Gateway -> main responsibility to take incoming API requests and route them to the correct server or the correct micro\nservice.It also does some other things we can note those, it does authentication, It often does rate limmiting.\n\nWhen we build up our High level design what we are going to do is we are just going to go one by one through our API requests\nand ofcourse our API request map back to our functional requirements. So we can start with \nviewing an event\n\nSo what would happen first client will going to hit our API Gateway. Our API gateway will route them to correct microservice\nWe are going to call this Event Crud Service so while its responsilbe to Creating, Reading, Updating & Deleting events.\nWe know most of these crud operation are out of scope for this problem we are just handling the view part and that would\nbe handled by this microserrvice. So the request is going to hit this service. and the service is simply going to read off\nof our database, this database is going to store core entities that we talked about. 21:00\n\n\nFor search we have search service , API gateway will send req to search service, search service will interact with DB and \nprovide the response back.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First thing in our design is going to have a client. Its going to be a User thats interfacing with our service. and then we\nare going to opt for a microservices architecture this is by default is most common setup in these types of interviews. If \nwe are not sure which architecture we go with Microservice is probably the right choice.\n\nApI Gateway -> main responsibility to take incoming API requests and route them to the correct server or the correct micro\nservice.It also does some other things we can note those, it does authentication, It often does rate limmiting.\n\nWhen we build up our High level design what we are going to do is we are just going to go one by one through our API requests\nand ofcourse our API request map back to our functional requirements. So we can start with \nviewing an event\n\nSo what would happen first client will going to hit our API Gateway. Our API gateway will route them to correct microservice\nWe are going to call this Event Crud Service so while its responsilbe to Creating, Reading, Updating & Deleting events.\nWe know most of these crud operation are out of scope for this problem we are just handling the view part and that would\nbe handled by this microserrvice. So the request is going to hit this service. and the service is simply going to read off\nof our database, this database is going to store core entities that we talked about. 21:00\n\n\nFor search we have search service , API gateway will send req to search service, search service will interact with DB and \nprovide the response back.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "d36RrQUqUvneyHuXgwv5h",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -147.51587086242762,
