    {
      "id": "eYbZGra2QubG4EdRTSvB2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 363.8259258032957,
      "y": 3139.7320625989305,
      "width": 613.7996215820312,
      "height": 45,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 303597424,
      "version": 463,
      "versionNonce": 925330780,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to Shard (split) your data?",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to Shard (split) your data?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "gUnavpOHuE772mgmTUoZq",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 375.3134308783568,
      "y": 3236.4247582908674,
      "width": 1232,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 779491696,
      "version": 1056,
      "versionNonce": 1129686628,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. What to shard by -> this is going to be field that we use to group our data, which we call it as shard key \n    Example -> If we shard by user_id that would be a column in our data and then all of data for the given user\n            will live on same shard.\n\n\n2. How to distribute data -> this is a strategy for mapping a shard keys values to a given machine to a given\n    database.\n    Example -> We mights split user_ids into ranges like we are seeing in above image\n                or may be we will hash them evenly across all shards as well",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. What to shard by -> this is going to be field that we use to group our data, which we call it as shard key \n    Example -> If we shard by user_id that would be a column in our data and then all of data for the given user\n            will live on same shard.\n\n\n2. How to distribute data -> this is a strategy for mapping a shard keys values to a given machine to a given\n    database.\n    Example -> We mights split user_ids into ranges like we are seeing in above image\n                or may be we will hash them evenly across all shards as well",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Fucc5xurbfiyqcD7FPbOA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 320.49863790016343,
      "y": 4028.9338121789215,
      "width": 1088.999267578125,
      "height": 135,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
