      "versionNonce": 1481305948,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678245,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This shard has Messi on it!",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This shard has Messi on it!",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2V2j8D-zxWTnSBxSti7PJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 259.6780605071601,
      "y": 12410.89343776912,
      "width": 1254,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 603478896,
      "version": 676,
      "versionNonce": 1503872100,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678245,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Hot Spots -> any time people want to see the post from Messi, profile pic anything request will go to Shard1. Now \nSuddenly Shard1 is out of order due to Messi is celebrity\n\nSolution ->1 Compount Shard key\n           2 Dedicatd celebrity Shard -> whenever we will see hight trafic we will move them to their shard.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Hot Spots -> any time people want to see the post from Messi, profile pic anything request will go to Shard1. Now \nSuddenly Shard1 is out of order due to Messi is celebrity\n\nSolution ->1 Compount Shard key\n           2 Dedicatd celebrity Shard -> whenever we will see hight trafic we will move them to their shard.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "tH_P843eAqo8KGysUsm7-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 356.9616348802201,
      "y": 13281.474096916978,
      "width": 1375,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1217573232,
      "version": 1880,
      "versionNonce": 2020385756,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678245,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Cross Shard Operations -> this usually happen when our query doesn't allign with Shard key.\nLike question is give top 10 posts across the plateform then we need to hit all shards, \nthe reality is we can't eliminate cross shard query completely,\nFirst line of defence is choosing a good shard key that aligns with our most common queries so that\nwe dont have them happen that often Even with the perfect shard key we still have the global query\nsomething like top 10 post need to hit all shards\n\nCommon Solution -> May be most common solution is we can cache the results of these expensive \ncrossshard queries, So we can use something like Redis with TTL may be 5 minutes, first time user ask for top 10 post\nit can be expensive due to it need to hit all the shard take top 10 post then filter top 10 among them  but not every time\nin this user may be see for sometime stale posts.\n\n\nAnother solution is we can denormalize our data. so that relation information will live together. Denormalization is process\nof repeating data such that you are making our queries quicker but in this case write will be complex due to we need to write\nin more that one shard. due to we have combined shard 1 and 2 now  both have same data we need to write in both places.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Cross Shard Operations -> this usually happen when our query doesn't allign with Shard key.\nLike question is give top 10 posts across the plateform then we need to hit all shards, \nthe reality is we can't eliminate cross shard query completely,\nFirst line of defence is choosing a good shard key that aligns with our most common queries so that\nwe dont have them happen that often Even with the perfect shard key we still have the global query\nsomething like top 10 post need to hit all shards\n\nCommon Solution -> May be most common solution is we can cache the results of these expensive \ncrossshard queries, So we can use something like Redis with TTL may be 5 minutes, first time user ask for top 10 post\nit can be expensive due to it need to hit all the shard take top 10 post then filter top 10 among them  but not every time\nin this user may be see for sometime stale posts.\n\n\nAnother solution is we can denormalize our data. so that relation information will live together. Denormalization is process\nof repeating data such that you are making our queries quicker but in this case write will be complex due to we need to write\nin more that one shard. due to we have combined shard 1 and 2 now  both have same data we need to write in both places.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GaINLiZ-Kmb3NiNDKZobT",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 362.4627252731408,
