      "versionNonce": 99471076,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Sharding in System Design Interviews",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Sharding in System Design Interviews",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "TB_xode1aNRE_3_WydZdM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 385.13747493680717,
      "y": 16382.996061417649,
      "width": 1143.998291015625,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIMj",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1452229520,
      "version": 961,
      "versionNonce": 1942356316,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Bring it up in deep dives when talking about scaling. But justify! \n\n1. Storage -> we have 500 Million users with 5 KB of data each and so that 2.5 TB Of data if a single Postgress DB can handle that\n    then we dont need to shard but we ended up growing 10 or 100 x then we would shard.\n2. Write throughput -> we are expecting about 50000 write per second but during peak a single database would struggle with this \n    write load so we would probably shard.\n3. Read throughput -> even with read replicas serving 100 million daily active users,making multiple queries each, we will need\nto distribute this read load across shards.\n do I reach any of the capacity limit, we need to determine that we can shard.\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Bring it up in deep dives when talking about scaling. But justify! \n\n1. Storage -> we have 500 Million users with 5 KB of data each and so that 2.5 TB Of data if a single Postgress DB can handle that\n    then we dont need to shard but we ended up growing 10 or 100 x then we would shard.\n2. Write throughput -> we are expecting about 50000 write per second but during peak a single database would struggle with this \n    write load so we would probably shard.\n3. Read throughput -> even with read replicas serving 100 million daily active users,making multiple queries each, we will need\nto distribute this read load across shards.\n do I reach any of the capacity limit, we need to determine that we can shard.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kT0shHVz8soFHlhEiTMPZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 388.7753946467802,
      "y": 16727.498566926573,
      "width": 1302.398193359375,
      "height": 180,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIMl",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1527141776,
      "version": 745,
      "versionNonce": 345657956,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What do you say? \n\n1. Propose a shard key based on your access patterns -> in a social media everything(post, profile) is centered around user so will shard by user_id\n2. Choose your distribution strategy -> consistent hashing\n3. Call out the trade-offs -> global queries will be expensive if we need top 10 posts we need to fetch from all shard and then filter 10 but\n    we can handle that using caching expensive queries or precomputing with backgroud jobs\n4. Address how you'll handle growth -> we can start with 10 shard which will give us room for significant growth but consistent hashing \n    will make it easy to add shards and reshard later if we need to.\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What do you say? \n\n1. Propose a shard key based on your access patterns -> in a social media everything(post, profile) is centered around user so will shard by user_id\n2. Choose your distribution strategy -> consistent hashing\n3. Call out the trade-offs -> global queries will be expensive if we need top 10 posts we need to fetch from all shard and then filter 10 but\n    we can handle that using caching expensive queries or precomputing with backgroud jobs\n4. Address how you'll handle growth -> we can start with 10 shard which will give us room for significant growth but consistent hashing \n    will make it easy to add shards and reshard later if we need to.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "htG09kzYDLa9LtGLFBV1k",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 387.12023714859345,
      "y": 16606.19461093432,
      "width": 1152.7984619140625,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIMn",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 780159344,
      "version": 691,
      "versionNonce": 1454732764,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "YOU DON'T ALWAYS NEED TO SHARD!! -> important -> we had a Postgress DB with 140 TB of storage thats a Ton, 50K writes per second so\nits sometimes in interview, actually it can be very impressive to show our interview based on this storage we dont need shard\n500 million users 5KB of data each, 2.5 TB of data we are going to have limited throughput so we dont need to shard.\n\nIf Sharding is necessary -> ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "YOU DON'T ALWAYS NEED TO SHARD!! -> important -> we had a Postgress DB with 140 TB of storage thats a Ton, 50K writes per second so\nits sometimes in interview, actually it can be very impressive to show our interview based on this storage we dont need shard\n500 million users 5KB of data each, 2.5 TB of data we are going to have limited throughput so we dont need to shard.\n\nIf Sharding is necessary -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
