    {
      "id": "ngczqn8aqh8OFcGNqVJz0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 349.465715358421,
      "y": 884.7191120023854,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bINl",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 3915944,
      "version": 283,
      "versionNonce": 32970980,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "traffic keeps on increasing our database is now not able to handle the load, at this poing the\nissue can't be solve by bigger database",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "traffic keeps on increasing our database is now not able to handle the load, at this poing the\nissue can't be solve by bigger database",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "n_xEEck_N9-0d2_YWaES0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 361.457902858421,
      "y": 1543.0120807523854,
      "width": 1078,
      "height": 375,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bINp",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1315413928,
      "version": 1161,
      "versionNonce": 256792412,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now we will move to Sharding, Sharding is the process of splitting our data across multiple\nmachines so that no single database holds everything and so each shard is its own standalone\ndatabase importantly, it has itw own cpu, own memory, own storage, own connection pool and it\nstores just a subset of the data such that together the shards form the full dataset.\nSo we can now scale storage and read and write throughput by simply adding more shards, And\nif we start to grow we will add shard4, shard5 and so on...\n\nNow importantly Sharding solved our scaling issue thats great , but it introduce new problems like\nhow do we choose how to shard? \nHow do we know which shard to route our queries to?\nWhat happen if we have a particularly hot shard?\nWhat happend if one goes down and we need to rebalance?\n\nWe have to deal with all this new operational complexity that comes from having multiple database\ninstances",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now we will move to Sharding, Sharding is the process of splitting our data across multiple\nmachines so that no single database holds everything and so each shard is its own standalone\ndatabase importantly, it has itw own cpu, own memory, own storage, own connection pool and it\nstores just a subset of the data such that together the shards form the full dataset.\nSo we can now scale storage and read and write throughput by simply adding more shards, And\nif we start to grow we will add shard4, shard5 and so on...\n\nNow importantly Sharding solved our scaling issue thats great , but it introduce new problems like\nhow do we choose how to shard? \nHow do we know which shard to route our queries to?\nWhat happen if we have a particularly hot shard?\nWhat happend if one goes down and we need to rebalance?\n\nWe have to deal with all this new operational complexity that comes from having multiple database\ninstances",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "RkoqaxWJKKYYz01i0YEjX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 384.0062969556432,
      "y": 3583.988317731547,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bINt",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 244917208,
      "version": 151,
      "versionNonce": 350903396,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In Simple words the shard key is  how we group our data and the distribution strategy is how we place \nthose groups onto shards",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In Simple words the shard key is  how we group our data and the distribution strategy is how we place \nthose groups onto shards",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qOGNsH-maek3d1x_MjWFc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 312.58495462609744,
      "y": 4615.184373166652,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bINx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1181676456,
      "version": 824,
      "versionNonce": 1254296540,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "High Cardinality ->  this is basically that we want a field with lots of unique values, so that we can\n    spread that data across the shards instead of piling everything on few shards, High cardinality means\nthat we can have a random or even distribution.\n\nEven Distribution -> Each shard roughly has same ammount of data.\n\nQuery Alignment -> Our shard key should match how we query our data\nExample -> If most of our queries are lets get all posts for a given user, then sharding by user_id, keeps \n    all of that user data on one shard, And it means we want to get all of a user's post. we only need to \nquery one database. We dont need to query all the different shards.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "High Cardinality ->  this is basically that we want a field with lots of unique values, so that we can\n    spread that data across the shards instead of piling everything on few shards, High cardinality means\nthat we can have a random or even distribution.\n\nEven Distribution -> Each shard roughly has same ammount of data.\n\nQuery Alignment -> Our shard key should match how we query our data\nExample -> If most of our queries are lets get all posts for a given user, then sharding by user_id, keeps \n    all of that user data on one shard, And it means we want to get all of a user's post. we only need to \nquery one database. We dont need to query all the different shards.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lbjWQRg75HyZ3075MUvJ_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 317.5018382455738,
      "y": 4985.020713055474,
      "width": 1144,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1401388760,
      "version": 200,
      "versionNonce": 2141794276,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "A bad shard key has low cardinality creates uneven distribution and it forces queries to hit many shards\njust to answer something simple in many cases.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "A bad shard key has low cardinality creates uneven distribution and it forces queries to hit many shards\njust to answer something simple in many cases.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KTGi0-fCJKvYVrPhGyjga",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 203.5713879393009,
      "y": 5584.230202579111,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIO4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 727942360,
      "version": 627,
      "versionNonce": 246231132,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569678254,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We have a popular social media app and most common operation is users visiting another users profile\nand loading all of their posts.\nIn this case sharding by user_id is a great choice because it has \nhigh cardinality -> Every user has unique id so we have tons of  distinct values to spread across\nthe shards.\neven distribution\nquery alignement -> for one user we need to hit only one shard",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We have a popular social media app and most common operation is users visiting another users profile\nand loading all of their posts.\nIn this case sharding by user_id is a great choice because it has \nhigh cardinality -> Every user has unique id so we have tons of  distinct values to spread across\nthe shards.\neven distribution\nquery alignement -> for one user we need to hit only one shard",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
