      "text": "Q why we cant make a function asynchronouse , why we need to use celery?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q why we cant make a function asynchronouse , why we need to use celery?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ocbSRqbza1K25tDiNM0Fx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -526.2088849647271,
      "y": 8387.840210444518,
      "width": 715,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 843963100,
      "version": 125,
      "versionNonce": 2015872860,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569696544,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "⚡ Key Difference (Interview Gold)\n\n| Feature              | Async         | Celery               |\n| -------------------- | ------------- | -------------------- |\n| Non-blocking         | ✅             | ✅                    |\n| Background execution | ❌ (not truly) | ✅                    |\n| Retry                | ❌             | ✅                    |\n| Persistence          | ❌             | ✅                    |\n| Scaling              | Limited       | High                 |\n| Use case             | I/O tasks     | Heavy/critical tasks |\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "⚡ Key Difference (Interview Gold)\n\n| Feature              | Async         | Celery               |\n| -------------------- | ------------- | -------------------- |\n| Non-blocking         | ✅             | ✅                    |\n| Background execution | ❌ (not truly) | ✅                    |\n| Retry                | ❌             | ✅                    |\n| Persistence          | ❌             | ✅                    |\n| Scaling              | Limited       | High                 |\n| Use case             | I/O tasks     | Heavy/critical tasks |\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kdF1mRaPtQfClbIbsW2DY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -519.1151349647271,
      "y": 8702.719116694518,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJr",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2047221596,
      "version": 127,
      "versionNonce": 921598940,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569696544,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "🎯 Simple One-Line Answer (Interview)\n\n“Async helps handle non-blocking I/O within a request, but it’s still tied to the request lifecycle \nand lacks reliability. Celery, on the other hand, is a distributed task queue that allows us to run \ntasks in the background with retries, persistence, and scalability.”",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "🎯 Simple One-Line Answer (Interview)\n\n“Async helps handle non-blocking I/O within a request, but it’s still tied to the request lifecycle \nand lacks reliability. Celery, on the other hand, is a distributed task queue that allows us to run \ntasks in the background with retries, persistence, and scalability.”",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kGbevdVNHRDfMvoOAozSL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -519.2791974647271,
      "y": 8848.082397944518,
      "width": 682,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJs",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 457298908,
      "version": 121,
      "versionNonce": 1139449948,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775569696544,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "💡 Real-Life Analogy\nAsync = Chef cooking faster in same kitchen\nCelery = Sending order to another kitchen with dedicated staff",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "💡 Real-Life Analogy\nAsync = Chef cooking faster in same kitchen\nCelery = Sending order to another kitchen with dedicated staff",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
