      "text": "How to create .env and access variable that are inside that",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to create .env and access variable that are inside that",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "rZ4H2j6BlThS1fJFyyF4v",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -526.7005866215909,
      "y": 10622.54678323419,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 800,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1214338712,
      "version": 214,
      "versionNonce": 2084113523,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775826026218,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 create .env same level as manage.py\n2 put variables that we want to put\n3 Install python-dotenv (or django-environ) \n    pip install python-dotenv\n\n4 Load env variables in Django \n    Go to settings.py and Add this at top:\n\n    import os\n    from dotenv import load_dotenv\n    \n    load_dotenv()\n\n5 Use variables in Django\n\n    SECRET_KEY = os.getenv(\"SECRET_KEY\")\n\nDEBUG = os.getenv(\"DEBUG\") == \"True\"\n\nDATABASES = {\n    \"default\": {\n        \"ENGINE\": \"django.db.backends.postgresql\",\n        \"NAME\": os.getenv(\"DB_NAME\"),\n        \"USER\": os.getenv(\"DB_USER\"),\n        \"PASSWORD\": os.getenv(\"DB_PASSWORD\"),\n        \"HOST\": \"localhost\",\n        \"PORT\": \"5432\",\n    }\n}\n\n6 Important Notes\n1. Add .env to .gitignore",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 create .env same level as manage.py\n2 put variables that we want to put\n3 Install python-dotenv (or django-environ) \n    pip install python-dotenv\n\n4 Load env variables in Django \n    Go to settings.py and Add this at top:\n\n    import os\n    from dotenv import load_dotenv\n    \n    load_dotenv()\n\n5 Use variables in Django\n\n    SECRET_KEY = os.getenv(\"SECRET_KEY\")\n\nDEBUG = os.getenv(\"DEBUG\") == \"True\"\n\nDATABASES = {\n    \"default\": {\n        \"ENGINE\": \"django.db.backends.postgresql\",\n        \"NAME\": os.getenv(\"DB_NAME\"),\n        \"USER\": os.getenv(\"DB_USER\"),\n        \"PASSWORD\": os.getenv(\"DB_PASSWORD\"),\n        \"HOST\": \"localhost\",\n        \"PORT\": \"5432\",\n    }\n}\n\n6 Important Notes\n1. Add .env to .gitignore",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
